The BOL is the Business Object Layer. 
It contains logic and functionality that are specific to the business needs of the software.
This layer should manipulate business objects that represent entities of the business.
Business objects are described above are simple POJOs and are defined in the 
BOLO which is the Business Object Layer Objects layer. 
The BOL should talk to the database via the DAL - Data Access layer.
The Data Access layer should give the BOL, BOLO objects and the BOL should give the
DAL BOLO objects. The DAL talks to the database however it wants to.